Security Core Subsystem (SEC-SUB) - Technical Specification
Internal Components
1. Threat Detection Engine (TDE)

Real-time Event Analyzer: Processes incoming events against behavioral patterns
Anomaly Detection Module: Uses statistical analysis and ML models for outlier detection
Signature Engine: Pattern matching against known threat indicators
Behavioral Baseline Manager: Maintains normal activity profiles per entity

2. Threat Intelligence Hub (TIH)

IOC Manager: Handles Indicators of Compromise (IP addresses, domains, hashes)
Feed Aggregator: Integrates external threat intelligence sources
Attribution Engine: Links threats to known actors/campaigns
Reputation Database: Maintains scoring for IPs, domains, files, users

3. Event Correlation Engine (ECE)

Temporal Correlator: Links events across time windows
Entity Relationship Mapper: Tracks relationships between users, hosts, processes
Attack Chain Reconstructor: Builds kill chain sequences from related events
False Positive Reducer: Applies contextual filters to reduce noise

4. Risk Assessment Calculator (RAC)

Dynamic Risk Scorer: Calculates threat scores based on multiple factors
Asset Criticality Manager: Maintains business impact ratings for systems
Vulnerability Context Engine: Incorporates patch status and exposure data
Business Impact Assessor: Evaluates potential damage of detected threats

5. Response Orchestrator (RO)

Automated Response Engine: Executes predefined response playbooks
Escalation Manager: Handles alert routing and priority management
Containment Controller: Implements isolation and quarantine actions
Forensic Evidence Collector: Gathers artifacts for investigation

Subsystem Interactions
AUTH-SUB Integration

Validates security decisions against user permissions and roles
Provides identity context for threat attribution
Receives authentication anomaly events for analysis

EB-SUB Integration

Consumes security events from the event pipeline
Publishes threat alerts and response actions
Subscribes to system state changes and configuration updates

SC-SUB Integration

Correlates threats across multiple user sessions
Triggers session termination for compromised accounts
Provides session context for behavioral analysis

AO-SUB Integration

Exposes threat intelligence APIs for external consumption
Receives threat feeds through standardized API endpoints
Coordinates with SIEM/SOAR platforms via API orchestration

SP-SUB Integration

Synchronizes threat intelligence across distributed deployments
Maintains consistent security policies across platforms
Handles offline threat detection with delayed synchronization

Security Workflows
Primary Threat Detection Workflow

Event Ingestion → Raw events from EB-SUB
Initial Triage → Priority classification and deduplication
Context Enrichment → Add threat intel, asset info, user context
Multi-stage Analysis → Signature matching, anomaly detection, correlation
Risk Calculation → Generate threat score with confidence level
Response Decision → Determine automated vs. manual response
Action Execution → Implement containment/alerting via RO
Evidence Preservation → Store artifacts and maintain audit trail

Correlation Workflow

Event Clustering → Group related events by entity, time, technique
Pattern Recognition → Apply MITRE ATT&CK framework mappings
Chain Construction → Build attack sequences and timelines
Impact Assessment → Calculate business risk and asset exposure
Alert Generation → Create consolidated threat notifications

